</emphasis>
paratype female from Cajamarca, Cerro Negro: (I) female tergum IX (T9) and tergum X (T10), dorsal view; (J) female tergum IX (T9) and sternite IX (S9), ventral view. Dotted areas (E–J) represent membranous areas. Circles in (D) represent the external opening of spiracles. Arrows in (I) indicate the external opening of abdominal glands.
</paragraph>
